---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve and peel @yellow onion{1};
grate one half on the largest holes of a #box grater{}. Thinly slice remaining
onion.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2
inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½
cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Return potatoes to pot and mash with half the @sour cream{3%tablespoon} (you'll
use the rest later) and 2 TBSP @butter{4%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4) until smooth
and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While potatoes cook, in a #large bowl{}, combine @organic ground beef{10%ounce},
grated onion, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, ¼ tsp
@nutmeg{1%teaspoon}, salt (we used ¾ tsp), and pepper. (You'll use more nutmeg
later.)

Form mixture into 10-12 1 1/2-inch meatballs (20-24 for 4) and place on a lightly
oiled #baking sheet{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and cooked through, ~{14-16%minutes}.

**Swap in organic beef for beef.**

Meanwhile, melt 1 TBSP butter in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
@peas{4%ounce} and cook, undisturbed, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir peas. Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly charred, ~{1-2%minutes}
more.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add
sliced @yellow onion{1} and a pinch of salt; cook, stirring occasionally, until
onion is browned and softened, ~{3-6%minutes}.

Add 1 TBSP butter and cook, whisking, until butter melts.

Sprinkle @flour{1%tablespoon} over onion; cook, whisking constantly, until
lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Slowly whisk 1 cup water into pan with onion. Add @beef stock concentrate{2},
@cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, and ¼ tsp nutmeg; whisk until cream cheese melts
and gravy has thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Remove from heat and whisk in remaining sour cream. Taste and season with salt
and pepper.

> If gravy seems too thick, stir in a few splashes of reserved potato cooking
> liquid.

Add meatballs to pan with gravy; toss to coat.

Divide mashed potatoes and meatballs and gravy between #bowls{}. Top meatballs
with peas and serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.